00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:09.000
Discrimination against individuals with disabilities continues to be a

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
serious, pervasive social problem.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Discrimination against individuals with disabilities persists in such critical areas as-

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Persists in such critical areas as employment, housing, public accommodations,

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:32.000
education, transportation, communication, recreation, institutionalization

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:37.000
health services, voting, and access to public services.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:47.000
Individuals who have experienced discrimination on the basis of disability have often had no legal recourse to address such discrimination.

00:00:47.000 --> 00:01:03.000
Individuals with disabilities continually encounter various forms of discrimination,

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:06.000
Including outright, intentional exclusion,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:14.000
the discriminatory effects of architectural, transportation, and communication barriers.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:21.000
Overprotective rules and policies, failure to make modifications to existing facilities and practices,

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:24.000
[music]

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:33.000
segregation and relegation to lesser services, programs, activities, benefits, jobs, and other opportunities.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:42.000
Census data, national polls, and other studies have documented that people with disabilities, as a group, occupy an inferior status in our society.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:47.000
[music]

00:01:47.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Full participation, independent living, and economic self-sufficiency.

